<br>
She gathered her belongings, donning her gleeming green armor and buckling on her gleaming scimitar, but just as she finished the last straps, something in the wind caught her senses and she knew there was going to be trouble this day, she put her hands out to her sides and called upon the forces of the earth to enshroud her in the guise of a great grey wolf, once the transformation was complete she called upon nature once again to encase her in protective majiks for the perils ahead, she then set off to the north where she felt the pull of evils drawing her....<br>
<br>
All seemed to be as it should be while she ran, she was to pass the great encampment of the Centaurs a proud race they are she thought, but as she grew closer to the encampment she realized something was amiss, great billows of smoke and fire came from the rooftops and buildings, as she enter the camp her wolf senses were overwelmed with the stench of death and decay and her heart was deeply saddened when she came upon the cause of this smell, hundreds of centaur bodies were strewn about the camp, the bodies were contorted and mangled almost beyond recognition, My god what could have down this horrible slaughter, I scoured the camp looking for survivors or signs or what could have befallen these mighty creatures but alas I found sign of neither, the marks on the bodies were not made by anything man made it was almost as if some creature tore them apart. <br>
<br>
Not long after I came upon the camp a fellow druid Tedule entered the camp also completely horrified by what had transpired, he told me that he had just come from the great city of the Aviak biredmen and it was the same situation, everyone was dead, but the question is how ?? What new evil lurks in the Karanas and can it be stopped before it reaches the civilized cities of Norrath.......<br>
<br>
<br>
