These short tales are meant to be continued by someone else so feel free to jump in :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/utandaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tandaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#993300>(10/4/00 4:28:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cold winters day</span><hr size=1> Tandaina ran as only a bard can.  Behind her the once prowd city of the bird people lay in smoking ruin.  Her eyes still watered from the smoke.  It seemed as if the very air was filled with a terrible waiting.  And <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> something</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> ran close behind her, hounding her every step.  She could see nothing yet it drove her north, always north. <br>
<br>
Instinct told her to run and not stop.  To keep going until the safety of Rivervale enfolded her.  But as she rounded a hill new plumes of smoke became visible. It was the centaur village.  The bard felt a groan escape her lips. She had spent long days within those stout stockades as a young bard, afraid and alone on a continent not always friendly to Wood Elves.  <br>
<br>
And so, though fear nipped at her heals she turned away from her nothern flight.<br>
<br>
Her drum carried her over the ground so quickly that in moments she was amid the ruin.  Tandaina staggered, retching, at the stench and the horrible slaughter around her.  She looked up and her eyes met those of a wolf who stood only a few feet away.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uthorpinwhiskyforge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorpin Whiskyforge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#993300>(10/4/00 6:04:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cold winters day</span><hr size=1>  Small hands clumsily pulled the fat body they were attached to out of the Gorge. The old dwarf was exhausted. He'd spent quite some time in the Beholder's Maze and had more than a few cuts and scrapes to show for it. He rooted through his pack to take another look at what he had taken from the Eyes.<br>
 <br>
A beautiful bracelet made of polished bone. It was remarkable to look at. Not much by way of protection for a warrior, but Thorp assumed he might fetch a pretty price for it. More than enough to sharpen his axe and take some of the dents out of his armor. He hoped he could sqeeze enough left over for a few beers as well.<br>
<br>
After taking another glance at his provisions, he came up with the idea of hiking down the road and heading onto the Centaurs village. He could think of no better place to have his things repaired, than by the same people who made them.<br>
<br>
After a few hours travel, thoughts of bartering and ale drinking ceased. Billows of black smoke clouded the sky. From the direction, it seemed to be comming from where he was headed. That put an extra skip in the short legs of Thorpin. His pack hit the ground, his walking stick swung up in his arms as the weapon it was intended to be used for, and he ran.<br>
<br>
About 20 yards out he realized the sad truth that he was too late. The smells of death assaulted his fat nose. Those smells werent fresh, and likely would become worse as the days wore on. He resolved himself to the gruesome task of burying a proud race of creatures, hoping he could find some survivors along the way.<br>
<br>
Walking through the encampment, Thorpin found 3 people standing about a shattered ruin. Maybe they could tell him what had transpired here, and who it was that could  do such a thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.threadControl?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub28.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="drinal28133frm1">General<option value="drinal28133frm2">Trading<option value="drinal28133frm9">Quests<option value="drinal28133frm10">Screenshots<option value="drinal28133frm11">Role-playing<option value="drinal28133frm12">Flames<option value="drinal28133frm17">Guild Information<option value="drinal28133frm4">Hate Raids<option value="drinal28133frm5">Fear Raids<option value="drinal28133frm6">Sky Raids<option value="drinal28133frm21">Growth Raids<option value="drinal28133frm22">Mischief Raids<option value="drinal28133frm20">Dragon Raids<option value="drinal28133frm16">Suggestions - Forums & Webpage<option value="drinal28133frm23">Epic Q